198
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:15,320
 In fact, his whole family were not believers in his day,

199
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:18,160
 something that was a little bit strange in those days

200
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,840
 as they lived in the UK at a time

201
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:22,560
 when there was great revival within the churches.

202
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,240
 But Francis and his family,

203
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,600
 Martha and the kids were not Christians.

204
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:30,600
 But on the 5th of November, 1809,

205
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,520
 Francis had a dream.

206
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:38,760
 And in this dream, he saw a room filled with people.

207
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:41,000
 And this room was filled with people

208
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,080
 who were intently listening to one person.

209
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:46,840
 And that person was what he could tell in the dream,

210
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,680
 a young English man.

211
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,200
 And he was standing on a small platform

212
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,880
 just raised off the floor,

213
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:56,320
 and he was holding up a Bible in the air.

214
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:59,080
 Now, this is quite a strange dream for Francis to have

215
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:01,240
 given the fact that they weren't, like I say,

216
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,320
 church-going family.

217
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:06,640
 But he could see this dream very clearly.

218
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:09,280
 And as the dream continued to unfold,

219
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,600
 he could tell that everybody in the room

220
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,760
 that was listening to the young Englishman

221
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:16,680
 who was holding up the Bible were foreigners.

222
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:20,600
 In particular, he could tell that they were Chinese people.

223
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:24,880
 After he had this dream, he woke up

224
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,960
 and he told the dream to his wife, Martha.

225
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:30,040
 And they wondered what the dream meant,

226
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:33,160
 because again, none of them really knew any preachers.

227
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,440
 They certainly didn't know any young Englishman.

228
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:40,440
 And they certainly in those days didn't know any Chinese.

229
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:45,720
 Now, that dream would have been lost to all history,

230
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:50,320
 unless of course, Francis himself wrote it down.

231
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,080
 And what is amazing in history

232
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:55,600
 is that Francis was an avid diary writer.

233
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,400
 And his diary has been passed down

234
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,880
 from generation to generation.

235
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,760
 This is Francis's diary.

236
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:10,080
 This came to me when my father passed away three years ago.

237
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:13,220
 And he gave it to me as is rightfully to be done,

238
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,760
 passing down through the family history.

239
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:20,360
 I wanna read to you Francis's entry on November 5th, 1809,

240
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:26,360
 some 213 years ago.

241
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:30,760
 He said this, "The dream seems strange to me.

242
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:33,880
 For I sense despite my lack of faith,

243
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,920
 a divine suggestion within it.

244
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:39,540
 The young Englishman seemed to reflect me,

245
00:09:39,540 --> 00:09:44,080
 or at least a future version of me.

246
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,160
 And the people listening intently

247
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:50,680
 also seemed to be in the future, many Chinese people.

248
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:54,440
