00:33:07,340 --> 00:33:09,660
 is to say, "That's crazy."

785
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:12,860
 In other words, that they will have the same feeling

786
00:33:12,860 --> 00:33:15,100
 that you had at the beginning of this sermon

787
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:17,300
 when you were like, "Wow, that's amazing."

788
00:33:17,300 --> 00:33:20,620
 Then he says this,

789
00:33:20,620 --> 00:33:24,220
 "This child is gonna be known by this.

790
00:33:24,220 --> 00:33:27,100
 His name will be Emmanuel."

791
00:33:27,100 --> 00:33:32,300
 Now that doesn't sound particularly amazing to us,

792
00:33:32,300 --> 00:33:34,060
 or perhaps it does sound familiar to you

793
00:33:34,060 --> 00:33:35,740
 because we sung it in a song earlier,

794
00:33:35,740 --> 00:33:38,780
 and we often use that name around Christmas time.

795
00:33:38,780 --> 00:33:40,940
 But I wonder whether you've actually ever stopped

796
00:33:40,940 --> 00:33:43,580
 to wonder why Isaiah mentions it here

797
00:33:43,580 --> 00:33:46,100
 some 500 years before Christmas.

798
00:33:46,100 --> 00:33:48,140
 His name will be Emmanuel.

799
00:33:48,140 --> 00:33:52,100
 Emmanuel means literally God with us.

800
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:54,780
 Here's the question you should ask

801
00:33:54,780 --> 00:33:56,900
 as a good biblical scholar.

802
00:33:56,900 --> 00:34:01,900
 Why is God being with Israel important in Isaiah chapter 7?

803
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:04,460
 And why is that also important

804
00:34:04,460 --> 00:34:06,620
 when we think about the first Christmas?

805
00:34:06,620 --> 00:34:10,540
 Well, we have to wind all the way back

806
00:34:10,540 --> 00:34:11,660
 to the beginning of the biblical story

807
00:34:11,660 --> 00:34:12,740
 to answer that question.

808
00:34:12,740 --> 00:34:14,820
 Are you ready for a bit of biblical history?

809
00:34:14,820 --> 00:34:16,860
 I know it's 11 o'clock, you're getting hungry.

810
00:34:16,860 --> 00:34:18,540
 You wanna go to lunch and visit the market,

811
00:34:18,540 --> 00:34:20,860
 but just stay with me for a few more minutes, okay?

812
00:34:20,860 --> 00:34:23,140
 'Cause this will blow your mind even more

813
00:34:23,140 --> 00:34:26,500
 than my story at the beginning when I lied to you.

814
00:34:26,500 --> 00:34:27,940
 In Genesis 1 and 2,

815
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,620
 right at the beginning of the biblical story,

816
00:34:29,620 --> 00:34:33,540
 we see a picture of what God with us looks like.

817
00:34:33,540 --> 00:34:36,300
 See, Adam and Eve were created to be in intimacy with God.

818
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:38,540
 They were created to be in His presence.

819
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:41,140
 And God is actually spoken of in Genesis 1 and 2

820
00:34:41,140 --> 00:34:44,020
 as walking in the garden with Adam and Eve.

821
00:34:44,020 --> 00:34:47,140
 He communed with them in the fullness of His presence.

822
00:34:47,140 --> 00:34:51,140
 There was this beautiful intimacy between humanity and God.

823
00:34:51,140 --> 00:34:53,540
 So much so that at the end of Genesis 2,

824
00:34:53,540 --> 00:34:56,940
 it actually says that Adam and Eve were naked and unashamed.

825
00:34:56,940 --> 00:34:58,900
 It wasn't just talking about their physicality,

826
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:01,900
 it was talking about their emotion and their mental state.

827
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:03,980
 It was talking about how they thought of each other,

828
00:35:03,980 --> 00:35:05,140
 how they thought of God.

829
00:35:05,140 --> 00:35:06,940
 There was nothing between them.

830
00:35:06,940 --> 00:35:09,540
 There was nothing to separate them.

831
00:35:09,540 --> 00:35:12,580
 There was this complete openness, a brokenness,

832
00:35:12,580 --> 00:35:15,460
 a vulnerability between themselves and the other.

833
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:19,620
 It was like nakedness without any shame at all.

834
00:35:19,620 --> 00:35:22,740
 And the Bible describes this as shalom.

835
00:35:22,740 --> 00:35:25,060
 The way the world is supposed to be,

836
00:35:25,060 --> 00:35:27,860
 the way the world was created by God to be Him

837
00:35:27,860 --> 00:35:29,900
 in relationship with Adam and Eve,

838
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:32,500
 walking in that garden, creating intimacy,

839
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:34,220
 where they were naked and unashamed.

840
00:35:34,220 --> 00:35:37,380
 It's like God is saying, "This is very good."

841
00:35:37,380 --> 00:35:41,060
 And then in Genesis 3, we know what happens next.

842
00:35:41,060 --> 00:35:42,380
 Through Adam and Eve's choices,

843
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:44,940
 they bring sin into the equation.

844
00:35:44,940 --> 00:35:46,700
 They disobey the obedience of God

845
00:35:46,700 --> 00:35:47,860
 and what God had asked them to do.

846
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:49,900
 And they bring sin and brokenness.

847
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:51,820
 And immediately everything is ruptured.

848
00:35:51,820 --> 00:35:53,940
 All of that intimacy of Genesis 1 and 2

849
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:55,140
 is completely ruptured.

850
00:35:55,180 --> 00:35:57,980
 And suddenly Adam and Eve start fighting against each other,

851
00:35:57,980 --> 00:35:59,260
 the first married couple

852
00:35:59,260 --> 00:36:01,180
 to have a bickering argument together.

853
00:36:01,180 --> 00:36:02,740
 They start blaming each other.

854
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:04,460
 Then they start blaming God.

855
00:36:04,460 --> 00:36:06,500
 Then they start blaming creation.

856
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:08,460
 And all of the intimacy of the relationships

857
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:11,380
 in Genesis 1 and 2 are totally ruptured in Genesis 3.

858
00:36:11,380 --> 00:36:14,820
 So much so that at the end of Genesis 3,

859
00:36:14,820 --> 00:36:16,740
 a statement takes place from God.

860
00:36:16,740 --> 00:36:20,740
 He casts Adam and Eve out of the garden.

861
00:36:20,740 --> 00:36:23,220
 And in doing that, it was his way of saying,

862
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:25,180
 because of the choice that has been made,

863
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:26,740
 the brokenness that is here,

864
00:36:26,740 --> 00:36:29,260
 there is no longer the ability, because I'm holy,

865
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:31,780
 for us to be present with each other.

866
00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:33,780
 And so he sends them out of the garden.

867
00:36:33,780 --> 00:36:38,500
 And basically God is no longer with us at that point.

868
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:40,780
 Are you with me still?

869
00:36:40,780 --> 00:36:44,020
 And really the whole rest of the Old Testament,

870
00:36:44,020 --> 00:36:46,380
 from Genesis 4 all the way to the end of Malachi,

871
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:49,380
 is a story of a people, Israel,

872
00:36:49,380 --> 00:36:52,460
 longing to be back in relationship with God.

873
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:54,740
 Wanting to be back in relationship with Him.

874
00:36:54,740 --> 00:36:57,660
 Wanting to know the intimacy that was there in the garden.

875
00:36:57,660 --> 00:37:00,220
 Wanting to feel that naked and unashamed.

876
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:03,420
 Wanting to know what it would be to be in a place of shalom,

877
00:37:03,420 --> 00:37:05,260
 where everything is good again.

878
00:37:05,260 --> 00:37:08,020
 And what you see in the Old Testament narrative

879
00:37:08,020 --> 00:37:10,380
 is God's people desiring intimacy,

880
00:37:10,380 --> 00:37:14,300
 and God Himself desiring to be close to them.

881
00:37:14,300 --> 00:37:17,820
 But because of the sin and the reality of brokenness,

882
00:37:17,820 --> 00:37:20,340
 there's this tension in the Old Testament

883
00:37:20,340 --> 00:37:22,540
 between a people that long for intimacy,

884
00:37:22,540 --> 00:37:24,740
 a God that longs to be with His people,

885
00:37:24,740 --> 00:37:28,500
 and yet now a necessary separation.

886
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:32,860
 So for example, God is with His people,

887
00:37:32,860 --> 00:37:35,060
 but now He's a burning bush.

888
00:37:35,060 --> 00:37:37,500
 And Moses has to stand at a distance.

889
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:41,020
 God comes as a cloud of fire on the top of Mount Sinai,

890
00:37:41,020 --> 00:37:44,220
 but only Moses is allowed to come up and be in His presence.

891
00:37:44,220 --> 00:37:47,260
 God comes in a pillar of fire into the tabernacle,

892
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:49,340
 but Israel are not allowed to go into the tabernacle.

893
00:37:49,340 --> 00:37:51,100
 They're only allowed to stand outside of their tents

894
00:37:51,100 --> 00:37:53,820
 and experience His glory from a distance.

895
00:37:53,820 --> 00:37:55,820
 Then God's presence comes into the temple

896
00:37:55,820 --> 00:37:57,020
 to the Holy of Holies,

897
00:37:57,020 --> 00:37:59,140
 and God is with His people like never before,

898
00:37:59,140 --> 00:38:01,460
 but only one person is allowed to go

899
00:38:01,460 --> 00:38:03,900
 into the Holy of Holies, and only on one day a year,

900
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:05,340
 and only after they spent weeks

901
00:38:05,340 --> 00:38:07,220
 cleansing and purifying themselves,

902
00:38:07,220 --> 00:38:08,660
 otherwise they would be consumed

903
00:38:08,660 --> 00:38:10,020
 in the Holy presence of God.

904
00:38:10,020 --> 00:38:13,020
 So yes, God is with His people,

905
00:38:13,020 --> 00:38:15,940
 but He's not really with His people in the fullness

906
00:38:15,940 --> 00:38:18,020
 that Genesis 1 and 2 suggested.

907
00:38:18,020 --> 00:38:19,420
 Are you tracking with this?

908
00:38:19,420 --> 00:38:21,040
 Why is all this important?

909
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:23,700
 Because by the time you get to Isaiah 7,

910
00:38:23,700 --> 00:38:26,540
 Israel has never been in a worse situation.

911
00:38:26,540 --> 00:38:29,260
 War, they split up as a nation.

912
00:38:29,260 --> 00:38:31,080
 There's now two different nations.

913
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:33,100
 They're dealing and struggling with idolatry and sin

914
00:38:33,100 --> 00:38:34,220
 like never before,

915
00:38:34,220 --> 00:38:36,020
 and they're wondering what's next for them.

916
00:38:36,020 --> 00:38:39,980
 And God breaks into the worst moment of their lives

917
00:38:39,980 --> 00:38:42,100
 and their history, and He says, "Guess what?

918
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:43,260
 Here's a sign.

919
00:38:43,260 --> 00:38:45,420
 I am sending a child to you,

920
00:38:45,420 --> 00:38:50,420
 and he will be known as Emmanuel, God with us."

921
00:38:50,420 --> 00:38:53,740
 In other words, it's happening.

922
00:38:53,740 --> 00:38:55,260
 It's gonna happen.

923
00:38:55,260 --> 00:38:57,580
 I'm gonna restore my intimacy with you.

924
00:38:57,580 --> 00:39:00,100
 I'm gonna restore that presence in your life.

925
00:39:00,100 --> 00:39:02,380
 You're gonna know what it is to have that awe

926
00:39:02,380 --> 00:39:03,700
 and that astonishment.

927
00:39:03,700 --> 00:39:05,660
 There is a time coming in the future

928
00:39:05,660 --> 00:39:07,860
 where you will know the fullness of the presence of God.

929
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:09,860
 And all of God's people began to lean

930
00:39:09,860 --> 00:39:11,760
 into the messianic hope,

931
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:14,780
 this future long for intimacy with God.

932
00:39:14,780 --> 00:39:18,060
 Oh, if this could only happen, if God could come.

933
00:39:18,060 --> 00:39:20,980
 And the reason why they wanted that intimacy again

934
00:39:20,980 --> 00:39:23,020
 was not just so they could feel nice and fluffy

935
00:39:23,020 --> 00:39:24,860
 and like they're floating on clouds.

936
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:28,040
 They wanted the intimacy 'cause they desired shalom.

937
00:39:28,040 --> 00:39:31,380
 They wanted peace on earth.

938
00:39:31,380 --> 00:39:33,840
 They wanted victory from their brokenness.

939
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:36,460
 They wanted victory from all of the danger

940
00:39:36,460 --> 00:39:38,500
 and the anger and the hurt.

941
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:40,020
 They wanted to be set free

942
00:39:40,020 --> 00:39:41,860
 from the things that were chaining them.

943
00:39:41,860 --> 00:39:44,100
 They longed to know the goodness

944
00:39:44,100 --> 00:39:46,340
 of what it was like in Genesis 1 and 2

945
00:39:46,340 --> 00:39:50,060
 to finally experience the goodness and the liberation

946
00:39:50,060 --> 00:39:51,380
 and the freedom of God.

947
00:39:51,380 --> 00:39:56,380
 So Emmanuel is not just a statement about God's proximity,

948
00:39:56,380 --> 00:39:59,520
 it's also a statement of his victory.

949
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:03,420
 When they heard Emmanuel, God with us,

950
00:40:03,420 --> 00:40:05,140
 it wasn't just like, oh, great,

951
00:40:05,140 --> 00:40:06,580
 God's gonna come and be with me.

952
00:40:06,580 --> 00:40:10,020
 It was, oh, great, there's gonna be victory finally.

953
00:40:10,020 --> 00:40:11,180
 I'm gonna know freedom.

954
00:40:11,180 --> 00:40:12,340
 I'm gonna know joy.

955
00:40:12,340 --> 00:40:14,220
 I'm gonna be set right again.

956
00:40:14,220 --> 00:40:15,820
 Are you still with me?

957
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:20,820
 Now, all of that sits behind the moment in Matthew,

958
00:40:20,820 --> 00:40:27,440
 the moment where God comes and does something crazy

959
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:29,540
 with a virgin, with a woman

960
00:40:29,540 --> 00:40:32,300
 who should not have been able to have a child,

961
00:40:32,300 --> 00:40:35,380
 just like Isaiah had prophesied,

962
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:39,020
 to a man who didn't really know what was next

963
00:40:39,020 --> 00:40:42,140
 or what to do, to a moment in Israel's history

964
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:44,460
 where they are under the greatest oppression and slavery

965
00:40:44,460 --> 00:40:47,260
 that they had ever been under in the Greco-Roman Empire.

966
00:40:47,260 --> 00:40:52,260
 And God shows up and Isaiah knows it.

967
00:40:52,260 --> 00:40:56,140
 Isaiah has prophesied this some 600 years before.

968
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:58,260
 And Matthew takes that prophecy.

969
00:40:58,260 --> 00:41:00,000
 And I want you to see what Matthew does.

970
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:01,020
 This is not arbitrary.

971
00:41:01,020 --> 00:41:03,500
 He sees Jesus.

972
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,740
 He understands the birth of Jesus.

973
00:41:05,740 --> 00:41:07,900
 And he's the first one in all history to go,

974
00:41:07,900 --> 00:41:09,620
 hang on a second.

975
00:41:09,620 --> 00:41:12,740
 This is exactly what Isaiah had mentioned 600 years ago.

976
00:41:12,740 --> 00:41:14,900
 And he takes the prophecy of Isaiah 7

977
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:16,900
 and he plants it right in his narrative

978
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:17,940
 of the birth of Jesus.

979
00:41:17,940 --> 00:41:19,220
 And he's saying, don't you realize

980
00:41:19,220 --> 00:41:21,300
 this is Emmanuel, God with us.

981
00:41:21,300 --> 00:41:23,940
 He's talking about the incarnation of Jesus.

982
00:41:23,940 --> 00:41:26,060
 He's talking about the reality that in Jesus,

983
00:41:26,060 --> 00:41:28,220
 we have fully God and fully human.

984
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:31,780
 You see, Emmanuel is not about God being near us.

985
00:41:31,780 --> 00:41:35,340
 Emmanuel is about God being one with us.

986
00:41:35,340 --> 00:41:38,500
 The incarnation is the representation

987
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:40,700
 of the greatest amount of intimacy

988
00:41:40,700 --> 00:41:43,200
 God could ever have with humanity.

989
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:45,700
 There is no more intimate reality

990
00:41:45,700 --> 00:41:48,220
 that you can have than Jesus Christ,

991
00:41:48,220 --> 00:41:52,660
 fully God, fully human, now merged completely as one.

992
00:41:52,660 --> 00:41:55,420
 That's the power of the incarnation.

993
00:41:55,420 --> 00:41:57,400
 That's what we see at Christmas.

994
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:59,580
 That's the birth of Jesus.

995
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:04,580
 And this incarnation sets everything else on its axis.

996
00:42:05,580 --> 00:42:09,460
 'Cause the victory is now here.

997
00:42:09,460 --> 00:42:12,500
 Jesus would go on in his life, death and resurrection,

998
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:14,380
 to pay the price for sin,

999
00:42:14,380 --> 00:42:17,380
 to stand in the gap as the only perfect sacrifice,

1000
00:42:17,380 --> 00:42:18,660
 the one to give up his life

1001
00:42:18,660 --> 00:42:20,020
 so that others could know freedom.

1002
00:42:20,020 --> 00:42:21,540
 He would, in his resurrection,

1003
00:42:21,540 --> 00:42:23,340
 show us that death is defeated,

1004
00:42:23,340 --> 00:42:26,060
 that we are now alive in the greatest amount of living

1005
00:42:26,060 --> 00:42:27,100
 that we could ever feel.

1006
00:42:27,100 --> 00:42:28,820
 And yes, we still wrestle with sin.

1007
00:42:28,820 --> 00:42:31,260
 We still sit in the reality of darkness around us

1008
00:42:31,260 --> 00:42:33,860
 as we wait for his triumphant return.

1009
00:42:33,860 --> 00:42:37,300
 But Christmas is God drawing a line in the sand

1010
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:40,580
 and saying, "I am now with you."

1011
00:42:40,580 --> 00:42:43,020
 You see, what was a messianic hope

1012
00:42:43,020 --> 00:42:44,620
 for everybody in the Old Testament?

1013
00:42:44,620 --> 00:42:46,300
 Oh, a time is coming when he comes,

1014
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:49,580
 is our present reality.

1015
00:42:49,580 --> 00:42:50,580
 And this is why,

1016
00:42:50,580 --> 00:42:53,180
 if we just casually show up for Christmas day,

1017
00:42:53,180 --> 00:42:54,780
 and we're like, "Yay, Christmas day,

1018
00:42:54,780 --> 00:42:57,060
 I guess I get presents."

1019
00:42:57,060 --> 00:43:00,020
 I think God goes, "Oh, come on."

1020
00:43:00,020 --> 00:43:03,060
 And I think you're more Ahaz than Matthew.

1021
00:43:04,020 --> 00:43:06,300
 And I want you to feel Christmas again.

1022
00:43:06,300 --> 00:43:08,380
 I want you to own it again.

1023
00:43:08,380 --> 00:43:10,020
 And here's what Christmas means to you.

1024
00:43:10,020 --> 00:43:12,820
 You are so privileged to live

1025
00:43:12,820 --> 00:43:16,300
 on this side of the birth of Jesus.

1026
00:43:16,300 --> 00:43:18,900
 'Cause for many people for centuries,

1027
00:43:18,900 --> 00:43:22,180
 he was just a hope, a promise for a better day.

1028
00:43:22,180 --> 00:43:24,860
 You're living in the better days.

1029
00:43:24,860 --> 00:43:27,940
 So when you come to Christmas,

1030
00:43:27,940 --> 00:43:32,940
 you come accepting his presence in all of you right now.

1031
00:43:33,780 --> 00:43:35,260
 In every single part of you,

1032
00:43:35,260 --> 00:43:38,260
 in all of your brokenness and your hurt, your messiness.

1033
00:43:38,260 --> 00:43:40,460
 See, Jesus just doesn't come to you

1034
00:43:40,460 --> 00:43:42,260
 when you're feeling good about it.

1035
00:43:42,260 --> 00:43:43,660
 He doesn't show up in your life

1036
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:46,780
 when you've got everything worked out nice and neat.

1037
00:43:46,780 --> 00:43:49,900
 The beauty of Christmas is that he's a present for everybody.

1038
00:43:49,900 --> 00:43:52,820
 He's here for all humanity.

1039
00:43:52,820 --> 00:43:56,980
 No matter how dirty or distant you might feel right now,

1040
00:43:56,980 --> 00:44:00,180
 the fullness of his presence is here.

1041
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:05,060
 The promise of better days are your days.

1042
00:44:05,060 --> 00:44:07,940
 So Emmanuel, God with us.

1043
00:44:07,940 --> 00:44:09,780
 Emmanuel is not for the religious.

1044
00:44:09,780 --> 00:44:12,940
 Emmanuel is not for the church.

1045
00:44:12,940 --> 00:44:15,820
 Emmanuel is not for songs that we sing.

1046
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:17,620
 You wanna know what Emmanuel is for?

1047
00:44:17,620 --> 00:44:19,940
 Emmanuel is for the drug addict

1048
00:44:19,940 --> 00:44:21,340
 who's struggling to keep his life together

1049
00:44:21,340 --> 00:44:23,300
 whilst he searches for his next fix.

1050
00:44:23,300 --> 00:44:26,100
 Emmanuel is for the single mother

1051
00:44:26,100 --> 00:44:27,940
 who's selling her body in one shot

1052
00:44:27,940 --> 00:44:29,260
 to provide for her family.

1053
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:31,020
 Emmanuel is for the investment banker

1054
00:44:31,020 --> 00:44:33,220
 who's struggling with suicidal thoughts

1055
00:44:33,220 --> 00:44:35,420
 because of a position he took on the markets.

1056
00:44:35,420 --> 00:44:38,820
 Emmanuel is for the refugee family

1057
00:44:38,820 --> 00:44:41,220
 who's embedded in difficult neighbourhoods in Hong Kong

1058
00:44:41,220 --> 00:44:43,140
 with racial overtones.

1059
00:44:43,140 --> 00:44:45,700
 Emmanuel is for your senior pastor

1060
00:44:45,700 --> 00:44:47,980
 who knows his brokenness,

1061
00:44:47,980 --> 00:44:51,340
 even amongst his best ability to lead God's people.

1062
00:44:51,340 --> 00:44:54,460
 And Emmanuel, mostly, is for you,

1063
00:44:54,460 --> 00:44:58,540
 for your story, for your narrative,

1064
00:44:58,540 --> 00:45:00,180
 for your narrative, your brokenness,

1065
00:45:00,180 --> 00:45:02,700
 your great highs, your great lows,

1066
00:45:02,700 --> 00:45:04,100
 for the great things that are happening in your life,

1067
00:45:04,100 --> 00:45:05,540
 for the messy things that are happening in your life.

1068
00:45:05,540 --> 00:45:08,220
 His presence is here.

1069
00:45:08,220 --> 00:45:11,540
 See, Emmanuel does not mean he is close when you deserve it.

1070
00:45:11,540 --> 00:45:13,540
 Does not mean he is sometimes close.

1071
00:45:13,540 --> 00:45:17,020
 It means that he is here, right here, right now.

1072
00:45:17,020 --> 00:45:19,620
 That victory is yours.

1073
00:45:19,620 --> 00:45:22,140
 That's Christmas.

1074
00:45:22,140 --> 00:45:24,100
 That's the feeling I want you to have,

1075
00:45:24,100 --> 00:45:26,900
 awe, astonishment, wonder,

1076
00:45:26,900 --> 00:45:30,780
 that you were chosen to live this side of Christmas

1077
00:45:30,780 --> 00:45:33,180
 so that you might be able to now walk

1078
00:45:33,180 --> 00:45:36,340
 with Emmanuel, God, with you.

1079
00:45:36,340 --> 00:45:39,260
 I wonder whether I could pray for you.

1080
00:45:39,260 --> 00:45:40,740
 Let's pray.

1081
00:45:40,740 --> 00:45:41,940
 Father, I thank you so much

1082
00:45:41,940 --> 00:45:43,820
 for every person here in this room.

1083
00:45:43,820 --> 00:45:47,140
 I thank you, Lord, for every family represented,

1084
00:45:47,140 --> 00:45:48,900
 every community represented.

1085
00:45:48,900 --> 00:45:53,100
 Father, I thank you that each person here

1086
00:45:53,100 --> 00:45:55,900
 is on the side of better days.

1087
00:45:55,900 --> 00:45:57,300
 And Lord, it's easy for us to experience

1088
00:45:57,300 --> 00:45:59,660
 all that we have in Hong Kong in the last three years

1089
00:45:59,660 --> 00:46:01,780
 and ourselves long for better days,

1090
00:46:01,780 --> 00:46:03,060
 and perhaps rightly so.

1091
00:46:03,060 --> 00:46:07,140
 But Lord, we don't have the same longing

1092
00:46:07,140 --> 00:46:10,740
 that those some 400, 500, 600 years

1093
00:46:10,740 --> 00:46:13,420
 before the first Christmas held in their hearts,

1094
00:46:13,420 --> 00:46:15,500
 because we're now walking in the time of your life,

1095
00:46:15,500 --> 00:46:17,300
 death, and resurrection.

1096
00:46:17,300 --> 00:46:18,340
 We're now walking in a time

1097
00:46:18,340 --> 00:46:20,940
 where your Holy Spirit is made available to us.

1098
00:46:20,940 --> 00:46:21,940
 We're now walking in a time

1099
00:46:21,940 --> 00:46:24,100
 where it's not just one person, one time a year,

1100
00:46:24,100 --> 00:46:25,740
 that can go into the Holy of Holies,

1101
00:46:25,740 --> 00:46:28,500
 but it is every person all the time

1102
00:46:28,500 --> 00:46:30,380
 welcomed into your presence.

1103
00:46:30,380 --> 00:46:33,380
 And so, Lord, I wanna pray for that for each person here.

1104
00:46:33,380 --> 00:46:34,820
 I wanna ask, Father, that you would move

1105
00:46:34,820 --> 00:46:36,700
 by your Holy Spirit right now.

1106
00:46:36,700 --> 00:46:38,860
 Lord, I pray that we would start our Advent season

1107
00:46:38,860 --> 00:46:41,500
 with this declaration of your presence,

1108
00:46:41,500 --> 00:46:44,100
 of Emmanuel, God with us,

1109
00:46:44,100 --> 00:46:46,020
 not drawing us back to the garden,

1110
00:46:46,020 --> 00:46:49,140
 but taking us forward to Revelation 21, 22,

1111
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:52,540
 to a new Jerusalem, a time where you will be with us.

1112
00:46:52,540 --> 00:46:53,740
 There will be no more suffering,

1113
00:46:53,740 --> 00:46:55,380
 no more pain, no more hurt,

1114
00:46:55,380 --> 00:46:57,380
 where there'll be healing for all the nations,

1115
00:46:57,380 --> 00:46:59,780
 where every tribe and tongue will confess

1116
00:46:59,780 --> 00:47:01,660
 that you and you alone are Lord.

1117
00:47:01,660 --> 00:47:05,020
 Lord, you are taking us that direction.

1118
00:47:05,020 --> 00:47:07,100
 Lord, may our celebration of Christmas

1119
00:47:07,100 --> 00:47:11,260
 still retain the awe and wonder of that first Christmas.

1120
00:47:11,260 --> 00:47:14,540
 And as we long for better days,

1121
00:47:14,540 --> 00:47:20,300
 may we not forget that we have our victory here in you.

1122
00:47:20,300 --> 00:47:24,660
 And Lord, we thank you for this in Jesus' name.

1123
00:47:24,660 --> 00:47:26,900
 Everyone says, would you stand with me?

1124
00:47:26,900 --> 00:47:28,180
 And we're gonna respond together

1125
00:47:28,180 --> 00:47:32,220
 as we sing once again of this incredible victory

1126
00:47:32,220 --> 00:47:33,380
 that we have in Jesus.

